org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.components.transformation.core.extensions

Interface IInstanceConfigurator


  • public interface IInstanceConfigurator
    Interface used by Qompass extensions that supports specific instance configurators, used for containers.

    • Method Detail

      • configureInstance

        void configureInstance(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.InstanceSpecification instance,
                       org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property componentPart,
                       org.eclipse.uml2.uml.InstanceSpecification parentInstance)
        configure an instance (within a container)
        Parameters:
        instance - the instance of an element which should be configured.
        componentPart - the property that represents the component within the enclosing composite. May be null, if the instance that should be configured is the main instance.
        parentInstance - the instance specification of the parent, i.e. the enclosing composite. If the instance that should be configured has a container, the parent instance corresponds to the instance specification of this container. This instance specification provides thus access to additional infromation available on the container level.
